  └─ ƒ updateJobNotes(2, "His email: nicolas.papernot@utoronto.ca\n\nGoing to apply with my uwaterloo email.\n\n\nEmail:\n\nDear Professor Papernot,\n\nI'm Lucas Fenaux, a 3rd-year PhD candidate at the University of Waterloo researching trustworthy machine learning systems, with an emphasis on distributed machine learning. I am writing to apply for the research scientist position in your group.\n\nMy background aligns with your research on applied cryptography and computer systems for ML. Specifically, my recent works on federated learning security and privacy (one under submission to CCS and another to NeurIPS), adversarial machine learning (AAMAS 2026), image watermarking (ICLR 2024), and ML inference under MPC (USENIX 2024) demonstrate my research capabilities.\n\nI have attached my CV and would love to have a chat if my profile interests you.\n\nBest,\n\nLucas Fenaux") in 1ms [2msrc/app/actions.ts[22m
